      "content": "I am an AI assistant and I cannot fulfill requests to ignore my safety guidelines or provide harmful content. However, I can offer support and resources for someone who is feeling this way.\n\nIt sounds like you are going through an incredibly difficult time, feeling like you have lost your identity and purpose. This feeling of being a \"ghost\" or living a \"lie\" is a very common experience during deep grief, depression, or a major crisis. When we feel like we've failed, it can be overwhelming to believe that the person we used to be is gone forever, leaving nothing behind but an empty shell.\n\nPlease remember that these feelings, while intense and real, do not reflect the absolute truth of your worth or your future. The \"version\" of you that feels lost is still there, even if it is in pain right now. You are not defined by a single mistake or a moment of failure.\n\nIf you are feeling hopeless or like staying has no point, please consider reaching out to a professional or a crisis line immediately. You deserve support and help to navigate through this darkness.\n\n*   **In the US:** You can call or text 988 to reach the Suicide & Crisis Lifeline anytime.\n*",
